/SCC/XXOMMENTARY/XX. חרפי רמתכ קידצֹ / the righteous flourish like the palm trees.
Unlike other trees, the palm brings forth each new branch from its very
heart. So, too, the /ITtzadik: tzadikim/XX reach outward from their very depths.
There are no superficial branches on their trees. The righteous are as open
as palms, as strong and straight as cedars. Such people remain fresh and
fruitful even in their old age.    /SC/XXA.G./XX/PR

